# 2002-05-07.mgs.3.br: Invitation of GNOME Foundation Board Representative as Advisor to SPI

May 7th, 2002

This resolution is superceded by resolution
[2004-08-10.iwj.dbg.3](../../2004/2004-08-10.iwj.dbg.3)

The resolution below has been accepted and unanimously approved at the
meeting of the Board of Directors of Software in the Public Interest,
Inc. ("SPI" hereafter) on May 7th, 2002.

__Whereas__,
we recognize that the GNOME Project plays a large and active
role in the Free Software community;

__Whereas__, comments and critique from important Free Software projects
will enable SPI to pursue its goal of furthering the development of
Free Software;

__Resolved__, that SPI hereby offers the position of an advisor to its Board
of Directors to a delegate of the GNOME Foundation Board, thus replacing
the GNOME Project Leader as described in resolution
[1999-09-21.mgs](../../1999/1999-09-21.mgs)
from September 21, 1999.

__Further resolved__, that the aforementioned advisor shall be appointed and
replaced at intervals decided by and/or at the discretion of the GNOME
Foundation Board.

